──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Open-core architecture
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

vonzio is built as two layers:

  • Data plane — the agent runtime, dashboard, chat widget, shared types.
    Distributed as the open-source `vonzio/core` repository on GitHub.
    AGPL-3.0-or-later. Self-hostable as a single-user instance via
    `make docker-dev-oss` (see README).

    Packages:
      - @vonzio/shared          types + cross-package interfaces
      - @vonzio/core-server     Fastify API + orchestrator + auth
      - @vonzio/dashboard       customer SPA (React)
      - @vonzio/widget          embeddable chat widget

  • Control plane — multi-tenant SaaS overlay (signup, invites, billing,
    plans, quotas, admin UI). Closed source. Operated at https://vonz.io.

    Packages (not in this repository):
      - @vonzio/cp-server
      - @vonzio/admin-dashboard

The boundary is enforced at the package level. The data plane runs
standalone — it has zero compile-time or runtime dependency on the
control plane. The control plane mounts onto the data plane at boot
via a dynamic import; when the control-plane package is absent, the
server logs "running single-user OSS" and continues. Six interface
seams in @vonzio/shared (ProfileResolver, IntegrationCredentials,
SecretVault, TokenValidator, QuotaConfig, UsageEmitter) let the
control plane swap default implementations with plan-aware ones.

This pattern follows Cal.com, PostHog, Plausible, Supabase, and other
open-core SaaS products.

